        <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="45" name="Message" rows="6" wrap="VIRTUAL">[quote]
Have any of you ever played a Dungeon game (MMORPG, MUD, paper and pencil etc) where spells and spell casting was such a complete pain in the ass?  I haven't!  I've played a lot of them from Wizardry in 1981 on my apple IIe to MUDS in the late 80's early 90's on local BBS's to EQ.  Honestly, I can't ever remeber so much difficulty

Lets take a quick look at just how difficult.

Lets just say you actually HAVE the spell and are trying to cast it:

A.  [i]You're spell is interrupted[/i] - Nothing like casting that long casting DOT only to find that a little bit of lag has made the server think you were still moving when you began casting.  Most people turn left or right before casting to avoid this but none the less - a pain in the arse

B.  [i]You're spell fizzles[/i] - I hate casting a spell and moving the mouse to do another task somewhere else only to have to go back and recast the spell.  Yes, patience can help here but I don't have any!  My favorite is when that level 1 lifetap you're pulling with fizzles.  You'd think I knew how to not fizzle that by now?

C.  [i]You're spell is resisted[/i] - The thorn in all casters sides.  I don't even want to get into this one.  I don't wanna get into the light blues in Grieg's resisting my lifetap and BOD.  Yes, VI did help with resists a couple months back but unless malo'd and tash'd, you still aren't going to land anything.

D.  [i]You can't see your target[/i] - Oh really asshole?  He's standing right in front of me.  Oh wait!  his toenail is partially obscured.  Forget the fact I just got nailed with an NPC spell from around 12 corners in a different room on a different floor.  People hunting Neriak ogres/trolls can appreciate this one.

I know I'm missing some here but I'll continue to the next part:  Actually getting your hands on the spell!!

A.  [i] Research [/i] - O.k., I guess it makes sense.  My beef is put the bloody words on lower level mobs than the level of the spell and put the words in certain locations.  How many of you have not had spells from 10 levels below you?  I didn't get HS until level 31.

B.   [i]Spell Drops[/i] - How many of you have gotten the group DMF yet?  Your new 56 or 59 pet yet? The illusionless ignite spells?  It is INSANE that pre-level 50 spells are dropping off mobs 10+ levels above the spell level and are super rare to boot!  Put the fekking things on vendors for Gods sake!  uberguy01 auctions, "EoT - 100k"

C.  [i]Useless Spells[/i] - I can't get over the amount of useless spells every class has.  Some of these spells are such a joke, I can only imagine the spell team sitting around a big round table in a dark room smoking crack and coming up with these spells.  I'm not even going to begin to list them, you know what they are.  I've got a ton more spells in the back of my book that will never be used than I do in the front.  I'm sorry but there should be NO post 50 spells that go to waste.

I love this game and I love my necro and I still have fun with him.  I know this is a big rant but i'm just venting a bit since Luclin is running like utter sh|t on my pc ;)  I'm not writing VI to fix any of this cause Lord knows they have about 10 years of things to fix.  Sorry for the long meaningless post

peace

[red][b]Fasz [/b][/red]
[black]55 Defiler [/black]
[blue][i]Bertoxx [/blue][/i]

